<p>David Szalay, a British‑Hungarian novelist, was awarded the 2025 Booker Prize for fiction in London for his book Flesh, winning the prize over five other shortlisted authors including Kiran Desai and Andrew Miller at the ceremony this week. The judges praised the book as “a &#x27;singular&#x27; and &#x27;extraordinary&#x27; work,” and the win marks a significant recognition for Szalay’s literary career. The announcement took place at the London ceremony that concluded the prize judging process for 2025.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/hgly06BSgKBHDMi5YR-tMFjIvR9AFswlFQp0BWKPvN1pvU4USwTATGcx9m-7UeV9chWq0zJ3uVz3DLHLRakDK0sQdIUDeX5EnKIN9rrSugpBAd2H36fl5i5mSOBFbxvLPUlJskB4hJK3bhklBEmD4faE7bH_YRlyhEgk1lIQwXcGNA4hHQ1IlDCQuzR7kX6Rc76K9n3yxO_rvmmZHE_XPcJkjCpgAWCPojzSUNtH2TIalcwf1EgoSR5V_MVPsWYCFZ2BrHKe5OZs' alt='Hungarian‑British author David Szalay poses with the trophy after winning the Booker Prize 2025 for his book &#x27;Flesh&#x27; at Old Billingsgate, London, November 10, 2025.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Prize payoff: The Booker award carries a £50,000 prize and is widely reported to give winners a pronounced boost in sales and public profile, often increasing backlist demand for the author.</li><li>Novel themes: Flesh is described by multiple reports as a dark, often tortured tale that traces a Hungarian émigré’s rise and fall and studies masculinity and ordinary life across decades.</li><li>Author background: Szalay holds British and Hungarian ties (sometimes reported with Canadian connections) and has previously been recognised by the Booker judges when he was shortlisted for All That Man Is in 2016.</li><li>Shortlist context: Among the five other finalists Szalay beat were Kiran Desai — herself a former Booker winner in 2006 — and Andrew Miller, underscoring the strength of this year’s list.</li></ul><blockquote>A &#x27;singular&#x27; and &#x27;extraordinary&#x27; work. - Booker judges</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Booker judges: The judges described Flesh as &quot;a &#x27;singular&#x27; and &#x27;extraordinary&#x27; work&quot; when presenting the award. (<a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/culture/article/2025/11/11/szalay-wins-booker-prize-for-flesh_6747332_30.html'>lemonde.fr</a>)</li><li>Literary commentators: Critics and reports have highlighted Flesh as a portrait of an ordinary man&#x27;s life in which what is left unsaid on the page carries as much weight as what is written. (<a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/british-hungarian-writer-david-szalay-wins-booker-prize-for-novel-flesh-9612045#publisher=newsstand'>ndtv.com / firstpost.com</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/11/11/david-szalay-wins-booker-prize-for-his-novel-flesh'>David Szalay wins Booker Prize for his novel Flesh</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/british-hungarian-author-david-szalay-wins-2025-booker-prize-for-novel-flesh-13949533.html'>British-Hungarian author David Szalay wins 2025 Booker Prize for novel &#x27;Flesh&#x27;</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/british-hungarian-writer-david-szalay-wins-booker-prize-for-novel-flesh-9612045#publisher=newsstand'>British-Hungarian Writer David Szalay Wins Booker Prize For Novel &#x27;Flesh&#x27;</a> - ndtv.com</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/culture/article/2025/11/11/szalay-wins-booker-prize-for-flesh_6747332_30.html'>Szalay wins Booker Prize for &#x27;Flesh&#x27;</a> - lemonde.fr</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/books/booker-prize-for-fiction-canadian-hungarian-british-writer-david-szalay-wins-with-his-novel-flesh/article70264694.ece'>Canadian-Hungarian-British writer David Szalay wins Booker Prize for fiction with his novel &#x27;Flesh&#x27;</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/europe/article/3332259/british-hungarian-writer-david-szalay-wins-booker-prize-london-ceremony'>British-Hungarian writer David Sza